  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best Salty Crunchy Kale Crisps. A British home-cook's dish, the kind of recipe families adjust across generations. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A weeknight-friendly recipe: most of the work is the prep, and the cooking takes care of itself.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Kale",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "200g - approx. 10 full stalks",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f5ya0058rkv4bg6hbm8k",
              "ingredientSlug": "kale"
            },
            {
              "name": "Avocado",
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "amount": 2,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f70j0074rkv4ixxmmyuv",
              "ingredientSlug": "avocado"
            },
            {
              "name": "Fine sea salt",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7kz0086rkv4lsr8ds3o",
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
            },
            {
              "name": "Cayenne pepper",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": null,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": true,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7tp008lrkv425asbnii",
              "ingredientSlug": "cayenne"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 450 F/230C.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Tear kale leaves from stems and then tear into smaller bite-sized pieces (about 5 cm in length).",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Toss in a big mixing bowl and drizzle with avocado oil. Massage to lightly coat kale evenly throughout. Sprinkle it with sea salt and massage again.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Line a baking tray with parchment paper and pour kale onto the tray spreading evenly throughout, so that there is no overlapping.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake kale in the oven for 5 minutes. (Check during the last minute to ensure they're not burning. They should brown a bit, but not go black). Remove from the oven and let cool slightly (1-2 minutes).",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Taste kale chips to ensure they're evenly crisp. If not, gently move kale chips around on the tray, and place back in the oven for one more minute. (Keep a close watch to ensure they don't burn).",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Transfer kale chips to a sharing bowl, optional to sprinkle with cayenne pepper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish.",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking, food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one, gentler than full blast.",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegetarian swap: replace meat with mushrooms, lentils, or beans, adjust seasoning to compensate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Spice version: a pinch of chilli flakes or cracked black pepper at the end shifts the dish without losing its character.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
